  "response": "Here are some great extracurricular activities that can strengthen your college application:\n\n1. Academic-focused activities\n- Debate team\n- Model UN\n- Academic olympiads\n- Science/math competitions\n- Research projects\n\n2. Leadership roles\n- Student government\n- Club president/leadership positions\n- Community organization leadership\n- Starting your own nonprofit/initiative\n\n3. Community service\n- Volunteering at local organizations\n- Creating community service projects\n- Tutoring/mentoring younger students\n- Long-term consistent engagement\n\n4. Specialized talents\n- Music (orchestra, band, advanced competitions)\n- Athletics (varsity sports, competitive levels)\n- Arts (advanced theater, visual arts exhibitions)\n- Coding/technology competitions\n\n5. Unique passion projects\n- Independent research\n- Publishing articles/blogs\n- Developing innovative solutions\n- Creating educational resources\n\n6. Internships/professional experience\n- Research internships\n- Professional shadowing\n- Summer program participation\n- Work experience in specialized fields\n\nKey tips:\n- Quality over quantity\n- Show depth and commitment\n- Pursue activities you're genuinely passionate about\n- Demonstrate leadership and impact\n- Maintain strong academic performance simultaneously\n\nRemember, Ivy League schools value well-rounded, passionate students who show genuine engagement.",
